   {
      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "@dooglus Signing proves you _receive_ at the address. Just because you receive at a given address, does not mean you sent the coins in a later transaction consuming the outputs (and indeed, the contrary is often true). Addresses are only used for receiving, not for sending.\n\nIf people need the ability to prove they sent a transaction, some new standard (whereby they sign with a transaction instead of an address) is needed.\n",
